	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=65101><span id=Scholar>Drienne, Guardian of the Glade</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>293 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.41]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The way recommended levels work, what you lose is a percentage based on the stat, and how close you are to the level.&nbsp;&nbsp;Usually, AC and HP/mana are the ones that reach full stats last, with resists and regular stats topping off first.  Since the AC is so low, and this item has no HP/mana to begin with, it's no surprise that this reaches full stats below the recommended level.<br><br>btw, I'm not sure *exactly* how the percentages work for recommended levels, and whether they follow a curve the higher the recommended level (as in, if an item as a rec of 10 and you're level 8, there's a much bigger difference than if the rec is 50 and you're 48 - the percentage difference is much greater), or if it's linear the entire way up.  This is just from personal experience.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76285 target=akztarg>Drienne Gardairne</a> -- 66 Ranger<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=316502 target=akztarg>Xide Kyck</a> -- 65 Necromancer<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=725442 target=akztarg>Hwel Jung</a> -- 65 Rogue</td></tr>
